{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "27", "m": "06", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "13", "M": "04", "S": "54"}}, "news": [{"title": "Mohali: Suntech City's developer in ED custody in \u20b9172 crore money laundering case", "para": "Realtor Ajay Sehgal has been remanded to three-day Enforcement Directorate custody in a money laundering case linked to the Suntech City project. The ED alleges Sehgal and others developed the project on land they didn't own, using forged documents for permissions, generating over Rs 172 crore in illicit gains. New facts have emerged, necessitating further questioning to trace the money trail and identify other involved individuals.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/developer-ajay-sehgal-of-suntech-city-arrested-by-ed-in-172-crore-money-laundering-case/132028506?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-225222/132028506.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Consumer panel orders Ansal Hi-Tech Townships to refund buyer left without flat after 12 years", "para": "A Noida consumer commission has directed Ansal Hi-Tech Townships Limited to refund a homebuyer Rs 1,00,762 plus 6% interest for failing to deliver possession of a flat booked in 2014. The buyer paid instalments over several years but never received the property. The developer did not respond to the complaint, leading to an ex parte order. The commission also awarded Rs 2,000 for litigation costs and mental distress.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/consumer-panel-orders-ansal-hi-tech-townships-to-refund-buyer-left-without-flat-after-12-years/132028350?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-372558/132028350.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Authorities issue fresh notices to over a dozen commercial establishments after deadly Lucknow fire", "para": "Following a tragic fire that claimed 15 lives, the Lucknow Development Authority intensified its crackdown on commercial buildings violating approved plans. Over a dozen establishments, including gyms, coaching centers, and restaurants, received show-cause notices. This action aims to ensure compliance with building regulations after the devastating Aliganj blaze, with further inspections planned.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/lucknow-fire-tragedy-authorities-crack-down-on-commercial-establishments-with-show-cause-notices/132028218?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-518482/132028218.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}